Singer Says Will Influence Koruna Only in ‘Extraordinary’ Moves

-- B y   P e t e r   L a c a
-- 
2011-10-18T09:12:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/singer-says-will-influence-koruna-only-in-extraordinary-moves.html
The Czech central bank “doesn’t
prefer” to influence the koruna directly on the foreign-
exchange market and would conduct such operations only in case
of “extraordinary” currency moves, Governor Miroslav Singer
said.  Singer was speaking in an online interview on the Prague-
based Patria.cz news server.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter Laca in Prague at 
